The paper proposes a new scheme for secure encryption and decryption of messages using fuzzy vaults and discrete logarithmic encryption. This falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of polynomial evaluation and projection, which are techniques commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper involves the use of random generation of keys and chaff points, which are techniques commonly used in computer engineering (cs.CE) and machine learning (cs.LG).
